    <!-- Hero Start -->
    <section class="bg-half-170 bg-light d-table w-100"
        style="background: url('images/tss_hero/tank1.jpg') center center;">
        <div class="bg-overlay bg-overlay-white"></div>
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row mt-5 text-center align-items-center">
                <div class="row justify-content-center">
                    <div class="col-12 text-center">
                        <div class="section-title mb-4 pb-2">
                            <h4 class="title mb-4">API Standard 2000 Venting Atmospheric and Low-pressure Storage Tanks
                            </h4>
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="row mt-lg-2">
                                    <p>
                                        API 2000 is indeed a significant global standard specifically focused on the
                                        design and testing of tank venting equipment, such as breather valves. Here’s a
                                        breakdown of its key aspects:
                                    </p>    
                                    <ul class="no-bullets">
                                        <li><b>Design and Testing Standard:</b> API 2000 provides guidelines for the
                                            design and performance of venting devices used on atmospheric and
                                            low-pressure storage tanks. It ensures that these devices are designed to
                                            safely relieve excess pressure and vacuum within the tanks.
                                        </li>
                                        <li><b>Section 5.4 - Production Testing:</b> This section of API 2000 outlines
                                            specific requirements for the production testing of breather valves. It
                                            mandates rigorous pressure and flow tests to confirm the valve's design
                                            integrity. Each valve must undergo these tests to ensure it meets the
                                            standard's reliability and safety criteria.

                                        </li>
                                        <li><b>API 2000 Test Report:</b> A critical component of compliance with API
                                            2000 is the API 2000 Test Report. This report details the results of the
                                            testing conducted on each valve, including performance metrics such as leak
                                            rates. It serves as proof that the valve has been tested according to the
                                            standard's requirements.</li>
                                        <li><b>PILOT OPERATED RELIEF VALVES:</b> Offering precise pressure control in a
                                            wide range of applications, our pilot operated relief valves are tested to
                                            ensure they meet stringent performance criteria.</li>
                                        <li><b>Certification and Quality Assurance:</b> It's emphasized that relying on
                                            generic certificates for tank venting equipment may lead to poor quality
                                            testing. Proper certification according to API 2000 ensures that the
                                            equipment meets stringent performance and safety criteria.</li>
                                        <li><b>Importance of Maintenance Knowledge:</b> Understanding API 2000 and its
                                            associated risks is crucial for maintenance teams. They need to be
                                            well-versed in the standard to ensure proper installation, maintenance, and
                                            operation of tank venting equipment.</li>
                                    </ul>
                                    <p>
                                        In summary, API 2000 sets the benchmark for the design, testing, and
                                        certification of tank breather valves and similar equipment. Adhering to this
                                        standard helps ensure the safety, reliability, and regulatory compliance of
                                        storage tank venting systems.
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div><!--end col-->
                </div><!--end row-->
            </div> <!--end container-->
    </section><!--end section-->
